SIMPLE: decimosexto
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Decimosexto
<hw>Dec`i*mo*sex"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prop., in
sixteenth; fr. L. <ets>decimus</ets> tenth + <ets>sextus</ets>
sixth.]</ety> <def>A book consisting of sheets, each of which is folded
into sixteen leaves; hence, indicating, more or less definitely, a size
of book; -- usually written 16mo or 16⟦deg⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decimosexto</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Decimosexto
<hw>Dec`i*mo*sex"to</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having sixteen leaves to a
sheet; <as>as, a <ex>decimosexto</ex> form, book, leaf,
size</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decine</ent>⟦br⟧
